      "Drill string hung off with 500k lb hook load",
      "Vessel drifted 750 ft from well",
      "ROV inspection of well, BOP, and riser",
      "Recovery of fallen pipe and MPD bearing",
      "Relatching to BOP operations commenced"
    ],
    "summary": "On March 5, 2024, at 04:15 hrs, the Transocean Deepwater Poseidon drillship experienced extreme unexpected changes in wind speed and direction due to strong thunderstorms while drilling the AW003 well in Mississippi Canyon Block 391. Wind speeds rapidly increased from 30 kts to 83 kts with multiple directional shifts (South to West to North), causing vessel excursion beyond the red watch circle limit of 90.3 ft. An Emergency Disconnect Sequence was initiated, resulting in release of approximately 2,875 bbls of synthetic based mud to the seafloor. During the EDS event, three joints of 6-5/8 in pipe and an MPD bearing (total weight ~13,200 lbs) fell from the derrick onto the driller's shack, causing structural damage. This falling pipe incident was not initially disclosed to BSEE and was only discovered during a subsequent inspection on June 24, 2024.",
